Instantly bought it to support the product, don't even care about the watermark. 
Haven't done anything productive all day besides crack myself up. 
Immediately went and bought a $35 model on Etsy and set everything up the way I wanted it.
Ridiculously easy to use, this program is amazing.
The fact that you can use this app without needing the use of launching it through Steam is brilliant. Steam usually closes your game when you're playing a different one through a different device.

Thank you for developing this lovely resource for the community. Absolutely support this project and developer. I've used this program an embarrassing amount in the last few months, and I only foresee that continuing in the future. It runs smoothly and without any issues, has more than enough options for optimization, and I've yet to encounter a feature that does not work as intended out of the box. Any issues I've had with the software have been from my own 'learning curve' journey and not with the software itself; and I've been able to figure it all out without too much need for research, etc. It's quite intuitive. 

Developer: If there is just one piece of feedback I can give - and I'm not certain how hard it would be - would be to support Linux with this program. However, otherwise this is lovely and I can't thank you enough for this program!

VtubeStudio:  ／人◕ ‿‿ ◕人＼ say no more

VTube Studio is a fantastic, free software that can be used to run any Live2D model.

With just over 1000 hours, most of those streamed via OBS studio, I can confidently say that this is hands down the best app I have used. The English translation from Japanese is great with no grammatical errors, so navigating the UI is easy. I have only encountered bugs regarding hotkeys, but those are fixed via restarting the program or resetting all emotes/expressions and are overall very minor and don't occur often.

Recently, I started using plugins with VTube studio to boost its performance, such as VTChaos, and Mix it up. With the API update, VTube Studio runs amazing and seamlessly with these plugins, allowing easy repositioning at the press of a button on a stream deck, changing "expressions" or adding items to the scene based on keywords said by viewers in your Twitch/YouTube chat.

One thing I wish was different was the ability to toggle a "condensed view" of your hotkeys. currently I have over 30 set up and its a little annoying to have to scroll through them individually to change or remove one.

You can add your own models, items, backgrounds by browsing VTube's local files and modifying the "streamingassets" folder <3
